# React SOP

- Functional components and hooks for new code; no class components unless legacy-only.
- Keep components small; extract custom hooks for shared state and effects.
- Props typed; avoid prop drilling — context or state lib per project convention.
- State: colocate; lift only when multiple consumers need it; avoid redundant derived state.
- `useEffect`: correct deps; cleanup subscriptions/timers; prefer event handlers over effect sync when possible.
- Performance: memoize only when measured or list-heavy; stable keys in lists; lazy routes for large pages.
- Error boundaries for route/feature shells; surface user-safe fallback messages.
- Styles: CSS modules, Tailwind, or project convention — no one-off globals.
- Tests: React Testing Library — behavior, roles, accessible queries; not implementation details.
- Before done: `type-check`, `lint`, `build` (or project verify script).
